generateSendableData

public AsymmetricCiphertextSendableData generateSendableData()
This function is used when an asymmetric ciphertext needs to be sent via a edu.biu.scapi.comm.Channel or any other means of sending data (including serialization). It retrieves all the data needed to reconstruct this ciphertext at a later time and/or in a different VM. It puts all the data in an instance of the relevant class that implements the AsymmetricCiphertextSendableData interface.

In order to deserialize this into a ByteArrayAsymCiphertext all you need to do is cast the serialized object with (ByteArrayAsymCiphertext)

Specified by:
generateSendableData in interface AsymmetricCiphertext
Returns:
the AsymmetricCiphertextSendableData object
